{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1781996727,"nonce":"+UjHslDjsoE5o2/nSVlsQmtn+w8=","title":"Add `CASE WHEN … THEN … ELSE … END` expressions.","message":"- v1: searched CASE (`CASE WHEN \u003cpred\u003e THEN \u003cexpr\u003e … [ELSE \u003cexpr\u003e] END`).\n- Deferred: simple CASE (`CASE \u003coperand\u003e WHEN \u003cvalue\u003e …`).\n\n- Builder: `case().when(pred, value).when(...).otherwise(value)` -\u003e an `Expr` of\n  the branches' common result kind. (Variable-length arms use the same cons-list\n  pattern as window `PARTITION BY`/`ORDER BY`.)\n- AST: `CaseExprAst` holding a cons-list of `(PredicateAst, ValueAst)` arms +\n  optional else `ValueAst`.\n- Type-level: all THEN/ELSE values must share a `Value` type; no ELSE -\u003e nullable\n  result (reuse `ScalarNullable`). `AstProjectionClass`: scalar (`ColumnTerm`)\n  when all arms/values are non-aggregate; aggregate when they contain aggregates\n  (CASE over aggregates is valid in grouped queries). Implement `NonAggregateAst`\n  iff all arms/values are non-aggregate (so a non-aggregate CASE is usable in\n  WHERE). Thread params across arms (predicate then value) then else, in order.\n- Rendering: new `visit_case` on `ExprVisitor`, implemented in both renderers;\n  dialect-agnostic.\n\ncrates/squealy/src/expr.rs (AST, builder, visitor method, class impls),\nrender.rs + squealy-test/src/sql.rs, lib.rs, + tests.\n\nRender (searched CASE with/without ELSE, nullable result), bind ordering across\narms, per-backend, compile-fail for mismatched branch types, `#[ignore]`\nround-trip.\n\nMedium (~one session) — branch type-unification + variable-length arms.","files":null}]}